 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A> at: 10/4/01 5:06:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numtini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/01 5:12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How much do you want Verant to coddle this server?</span><hr size=1> A &quot;straw man&quot; is a method of argument in which you take a hopelessly weak charicature of your opponent's point of view, and then proceed to rip it apart, not on the weakness of your opponents actual point of view, but on the weakness of the hyperbolic elements that you have injected into the charicture.<br>
<br>
In other words, instead of fighting a real man, you build a straw man and then knock the stuffing out of it. Then you declare victory.<br>
<br>
On the FV boards the classic has already arisen: the argument that &quot;RP Fanatics are requiring everyone to use thee and thou.&quot; Obviously one would have to be a fanatic to advocate this. Nobody could possibly agree that thee and thou and other archaic terms are required. It therefore becomes extremely easy to declare that those persons advocating those views are insane, irrational, and extremist. Because if they were advocating any such thing they would be. This then gives the appearance of a rhetorical victory as well as winning the sympathy of those who would see this as extreme.<br>
<br>
Problem is, no pro-roleplayer has advocated any such thing or anything even close. It is a straw man.<br>
<br>
 <p>Numtini Lightheart <br>
