noun <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> <br>
   (the use of) remarks which clearly mean the opposite of what they say, and which are made in order to hurt someone's feelings or to criticize something in an amusing way.</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
   I think you're mistaking a lot of the above for &quot;straw men&quot;.<br>
<br>
- Dysharmony Dyschord<br>
Drunken Bard of Rallos Zek<br>
<br>
PS: Here's the non-sarcastic version so you don't think I'm beating up straw.<br>
<br>
1) Some people here claim that non-role players detrimentally impact their role-playing experience.<br>
2) Some of those same people want Verant to remove those who have no interest in role-playing from the RP server.<br>
3) Some other people want the ability to vote non-roleplayers off of the server.<br>
4) Those same people have the ability to ignore the afforementioned non-RPers.<br>
5) As the RP server has a different rules-set, it's likely to attract people who enjoy the new rules set, but don't really care much about RP.<br>
6) As the first new (non-PvP) server in almost a year, many players new to EQ (purchased the game since X-mas or later) will want to try the experience of starting on a fresh new server, and are drawn to this rather than RP.<br>
7) Because several people have legitimate reasons for wanting to play on FV, not all of them wanting to roleplay, the easiest way to keep the environment full of RP is to try and involve non-RPers in your fiction, and just ignore them if they don't want to be a part of it.<br>
<br>
